Hong Kong Tycoon Continues Commitment To Education
SHANTOU , November 19 ( Xinhua ) -- The prominent Hong Kong entrepreneur , Li Ka-Shing , said here today he is happy to spend money and time in helping education .
At a board meeting of Shantou University today , Li said that education and medical developments serve the long-term interests of human beings and that the Asian financial turmoil will not discourage him from giving financial support to the university .
Shantou University was founded by Li in 1981 .
Since then , he has spent 1.2 billion Hong Kong dollars on it .
The schools was listed by the Ministry of Education as one of the 100 institutions of higher learning of China that will be up to international standards by the year 2000 .
